  "description": "David Johan Karl Magnusson was a Swedish civil engineer born on November 14, 1898, in Gothenburg. He completed his studies at Chalmers University of Technology in 1924. Throughout his career, he worked at various organizations including the City Street Office, Sanitation Department, City Engineering Office, and Gothenburg's City Property Management Office, where he served as the chief engineer and head of the street planning department from 1938. He was also affiliated with the Technical Society, Department of Road and Water Engineering, starting from 1943. David was married twice, first to Ruth Karlgren in 1924 until her death in 1932, and then to Greta Lindeli in 1936. He had five children named Britt-Marie, Ingela, Anita, Margareta, and Karl-Magnus. David had a hobby of sailing and he enjoyed traveling to Finland, Norway, Denmark, Germany, and Russia in 1934."
